The paper deals with natural language processing and database querying, which are both topics within the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper specifically focuses on improving the performance of text-to-SQL models, which are used to translate natural language questions into SQL queries, making it likely that the paper also falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). The proposed re-ranker model is based on BERT, a popular deep learning model for natural language processing, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves analyzing and optimizing the performance of the text-to-SQL and re-ranker models, which could fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
